Date: 5/4/1865
Source: Daily Southern Cross
Author:
Vol / Page: 5
Edition:
Quote: A question was put to Dr Monro at the end of the meeting, whether he would object to an export duty on wool, and an import duty on sheep-wash tobacco and wool packs. The honorable member, in reply, said that he had no objection to tax wool in common with other exports, but he objected to a tax on sheep-wash tobacco.
